title: US Indexes Rebound for Closing Gains Friday
text: The Dow Jones Industrial Average closed at 31,496.30 on Friday with a gain of 572.16 points or 1.85%. The S&P 500 closed at 3,841.94 for a gain of 73.47 points or 1.95%.

title: REITs Cool On Overheating Fears
text: U.S. equity markets were mostly higher on a volatile week as investors remain skittish about a potential "overheating" U.S. economy and the implications for interest rates, inflation, and equity valuations. Bouncing back following two weeks of declines, the S&P 500 gained 0.9% on the week, but the tech-heavy Nasdaq 100 dipped another 1.7% and briefly dipped into "correction territory."

title: Stocks Had a Wild Week, But Money Kept Flowing Into Equities. What to Know.
text: It's a sign that optimism is holding strong on an already richly-valued market.

title: Stock Market Analysis: Surging Volume, Rising Rates, and Trading Setups
text: Wow, what a week in the financial markets. Interest rates spook pushed volume higher and tech stocks reversed higher out of its recent swoon.

title: Senate Alters Unemployment Benefits Before Passing Stimulus Package
text: Enhanced unemployment compensation remains the same, but payments will last longer and a new tax break is added.

title: Economic Preview: The U.S. economy is ready to surge again. So is inflation
text: The U.S. added a robust 379,000 jobs in February and the economy is primed to take off, but improved growth prospects might come with a cost in the short run: Rising inflation.

title: The Week On Wall Street: It's Hard To Stop A Bull Market
text: The story remains the same - Global economic data is at or near multi-year highs. The recovery continues. Earnings season wraps up with record results. More companies now have a good idea of what we can expect next.

title: Market Snapshot: Housing is a luxury? Here's what the K-shaped recovery means for real estate
text: A K-shaped recovery from the COVID-induced downturn could be accompanied by an increasingly unequal housing market.

title: Two Sessions: Amid Uncertainty, China's Quest For Bold Development
text: At a historical moment of hope and uncertainty, China pledges bold economic development despite global tensions. China's annual "Two Sessions" meeting has approved national priorities for 2021.

title: U.S. IPO Weekly Recap: New Issuers See Mixed Returns In A 2 IPO Week
text: Activity in the IPO market started to pick up this past week, with two IPOs raising $1.8 billion. Blank checks kept up their neck-breaking pace, with 39 SPACs raising $11.1 billion.

title: Weekly High Frequency Indicators: Interest Rates Cause Long-Term Forecast To Change
text: High frequency indicators can give us a nearly up-to-the-moment view of the economy. The metrics are divided into long leading, short leading, and coincident indicators.

title: Testing The Fed
text: The bond vigilantes are pushing rates higher, testing the Fed's resolve to maintain an overly accommodative policy. All this while the economy picks up steam along with inflationary expectations.

title: Treasury Yields Surge Amid U.S. Stimulus Expectations
text: Two factors behind the latest rise in U.S. government bond yields. Tech stocks sell off as interest rates grind higher. U.S. adds 379,000 jobs in strong February showing.

title: S&P 500 Weekly Earnings Update: Revisions Continue Higher, But Entering Quiet Period
text: Like the last 12 weeks and even longer, the upward revisions to forward quarter growth rates should portend favorable for "the market" in 2021. Rising rates are definitely spooking investors, and compressing valuations on the mega-cap growth stocks.

title: U.S. gains 379K jobs in February, jobless rate at 6.2%
